>>    This overlooks the fact that routine use of encryption enhances the
>>  security of the messages that really need secrecy; the latter are less
>>  noticable that way.

>Wouldn't this also greatly 'enhance' the overhead involved in sending messages
>across the net?

Wouldn't it decrease the overhead, since pgp-encrypted messages are
compressed before encryption?  Unless the messages are short, when adding a
signature could negate the compression savings.

